ANC Leader Musalia Mudavadi Has Launched A Autobiography Of His Life Detailing His Upbringing, Education And His Political Career, With A Call To His Peers To Also Tell Their Stories. Mudavadi Launched The Book Titled Soaring Above The Storms Of Passion In An Event Attended By Among Others Wiper Leader Kalonzo Musyoka, Ford Kenya’s Moses Wetangula And Sports Cabinet Secretary Amina Mohammed. The Book, Co Authored With Anc Secretary General Barrack Muluka, Details Among Other Issues, Mudavadi’s Thrust To Politics, And His Experience Under Retired Presidents Daniel Moi And Mwai Kibaki’s Administrations, As Well His Recent Alleged Betrayal By ODM Leader Raila Odinga.